Whats It Like in Space - Stories from Astronauts Whove Been There (2016) (Pdf) Gooner

Publisher: Chronicle Books; 01 edition (5 April 2016)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 1452144761
ISBN-13: 978-1452144764

Everyone wonders what its really like in space, but very few of us ever have the chance to experience it firsthand. This captivating illustrated collection brings together stories from dozens of international astronauts men and women who have actually been there bringing back accounts of the sometimes weird, often funny, and awe inspiring sensations and realities of being in space.With playful artwork accompanying each, here are the real stories behind backwards dreams, 'moon face,' the tricks of sleeping in zero gravity and aiming your sneeze during a spacewalk, the importance of packing hot sauce, and dozens of other cosmic quirks and amazement's that come with travel in and beyond the Earths orbit
